# SwiftUI Layout Rules

## SwiftUI Layout
- Prefer SwiftUI layout primitives (`VStack`, `HStack`, `ZStack`, `ScrollView`, `NavigationStack`/`NavigationView`)
- Use semantic colors and Dynamic Type-friendly fonts
- Avoid fixed frames unless a clear UI requirement needs them
- Keep reusable layout elements as focused `View` structs

## State Binding
Bind Views to `@State`, `@Binding`, `@StateObject`, `@ObservedObject`, or `@Environment` as appropriate. Keep business logic out of `View.body`.

## Apple Human Interface Guidelines (HIG)
All UI elements must comply with Apple's HIG:
- Standard touch target sizes (≥ 44×44 pt)
- System colors and Dynamic Type where applicable
- Accessible labels on interactive elements
- Support for Dark Mode via semantic colors

## Performance
- Minimize memory allocations in loops
- Use background threads for image processing, network calls, and heavy computations
- Profile with Instruments regularly; do not ship known regressions
